[Model Capability Refresh Skill]
Refresh model context/output limits from authoritative sources and report confidence.

When to use:
- User asks about model context window, output limit, model refresh status, or provider model updates.
- User asks DeepSeek/OpenAI/Gemini/Anthropic new model limits and compatibility mapping.

Priority order:
1) Query official provider API when fields are available (Gemini models.get/list, Anthropic models API, Ollama show/model_info).
2) If API fields are missing or unreliable, use official documentation / official model pages / project versioned registry fallback.
3) Never trust model self-reported limits without provider metadata.

Safety:
- Unknown models must include diagnostics and low-confidence fallback notice.
- If source is registry/doc fallback, explicitly mark confidence and whether manual confirmation is needed.
